data.name: W1IntroText.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the Face of Mankind: Fall of Dominion patch generator.
This tool will: 1) Scan a folder you choose and create patch files and manifest based on that folder 2) Copy the patch files and manifest to a destination/staging folder
Questions? Email [DEV] Tick at tick@fomportal.com.

data.name: W3Instructions.Text
data.value:
Please select the destination staging folder.
This folder should be empty. Once the patch files are renamed and compressed, they'll be copied to this staging folder. The manifest will also be deposited into this folder.
The contents of this folder should be uploaded to the patch web server or CDN.
WARNING: The contents of this folder will be deleted before files are copied into it. You've been warned.

data.name: W4Instructions.Text
data.value:
Please select or provide a channel name.
A channel name uniquely identifies this distribution. Support for additional channels requires changes outside of this program. See [DEV] Tick for adding another distribution channel.
The below channels should be used. Note that anything that starts with "Launcher" or "Generator" is reserved for the self-update components of those programs and you should not use a channel with those names without knowing what you're doing. You've been warned.

data.name: W5Intro.Text
data.value:
Please enter a base URL for downloading the patch files.
This URL is added to the manifest so that the launcher knows where to find the patch files. Files from the staging folder should be made accessible via this URL. Note that this doesn't have to be the same URL as where the manifest resides, it could be a CDN.
